# ~/.localrc — machine-specific configuration, not tracked by git
# Copy this file to ~/.localrc and uncomment the values you want to change.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Language
# Language for dotfiles shell functions (extract/extraer, compress/comprimir).
# Supported: en (default), es
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DOTFILES_LANG="en"     # "es" enables: extraer=extract, comprimir=compress

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Login banner
# Show the dotfiles logo on shell login.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DOTFILES_SHOW_LOGO=0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Privilege escalation
# Prefix for package manager commands. Leave unset to use sudo by default.
# Set to "" to run without sudo (e.g. if you are root).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IFSUDO="sudo"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default applications
# Used by file extension associations in zsh (alias -s).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BROWSER="firefox"
if command -v emacs >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  EDITOR="emacs"
else
  EDITOR="vim"
fi
# VISOR="feh"
# OFFICESUITE="libreoffice"
# PDFVIEWER="papers"          # GNOME 3+; use "evince" on older systems
# GIMP="gimp"
# SVG_EDITOR="inkscape"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Projects directory
# Base path for your code projects.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PROJECTS="$HOME/Projects"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pager
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PAGER="less"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Display resolution toggle (`res` function)
# RES_MODE_A/RES_MODE_B hold an argument string for your platform's backend;
# `res` toggles between them. Run `res` with neither set to print the current
# layout. Backends:
#   macOS         displayplacer   (brew install displayplacer; see `displayplacer list`)
#   Linux/X11     xrandr          (covers XFCE, LXQt, GNOME-on-Xorg)
#   Linux/Wayland wlr-randr | gnome-randr | kscreen-doctor
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS (displayplacer — one quoted arrangement string per mode):
# RES_MODE_A="id:XXXX res:1440x900 hz:60 color_depth:8 scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0"
# RES_MODE_B="id:XXXX res:1920x1200 hz:60 color_depth:8 scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0"
#
# X11 (xrandr — run `xrandr` to list outputs/modes):
# RES_MODE_A="--output eDP-1 --mode 1440x900"
# RES_MODE_B="--output eDP-1 --mode 1920x1080"
#
# Wayland — wlroots/sway (wlr-randr) or GNOME (gnome-randr); both take the same
# xrandr-style flags. Run the tool with no args to list outputs/modes.
# NOTE: plain xrandr does NOT work under Wayland (it only drives Xwayland), so
# GNOME-on-Wayland needs gnome-randr installed; without it `res` points you to
# Settings instead.
# RES_MODE_A="--output eDP-1 --mode 1440x900"
# RES_MODE_B="--output eDP-1 --mode 1920x1080"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local PATH additions
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
